Ireland’s NAMA Sells London Hotel Loans, Broadcaster RTE Says

-- B y   D a r a   D o y l e
-- 
2011-09-29T11:48:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/ireland-s-nama-sells-london-hotel-loans-broadcaster-rte-says.html
Ireland’s National Asset Management
Agency sold loans associated with London hotels, Claridges, the
Connaught and the Berkeley, state broadcaster RTE said. The
agency sold the loans for more than 800 million euros, the
Dublin-based broadcaster said on its Web site.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dara Doyle at 
 ddoyle1@bloomberg.net  